-- Taiwan Stocks: AU Optronics, Powerchip, Taiwan Life Insurance
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-14T01:59:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/taiwan-stocks-au-optronics-powerchip-taiwan-life-insurance.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:32 a.m. local time in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 1.4 percent to 8,141.04.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) fell 1 percent to NT$15.70
after a federal jury in  San Francisco  found a vice chairman and
a senior vice president guility of colluding with rivals to fix
prices. AU Optronics said it will appeal the verdict and a fine
that it expects to be issued within the next few months.  Powerchip Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT) gained 3.2 percent to
NT$1.28. The chipmaker got agreements from 41 lenders to extend
mid- to long-term loans by one year, according to a statement to
the Taiwan stock exchange.  Taiwan Life Insurance Co. (2823)  (2833 TT) increased 1.7 percent
to NT$21.20, set for the highest close since Feb. 13. The
company got a $100 million quota as a Qualified Foreign
Institutional Investor from  China â€™s State Administration of
Foreign Exchange, according to a statement to the Taiwan stock
